ic <b>Ó Muireadhaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Muireadhach</i>’ a personal name meaning ‘mariner’. Occasionally it may be a shortened form of   McMurray  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Murri","meanings":["Probably Scottish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murry","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murrah","meanings":["Probably an altered form of Scottish   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murie","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Michel.","Scottish: habitational name from Murie in Errol (Perthshire).","Scottish and Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Merhi","meanings":["Arabic (mainly Lebanon and Syria): from a variant of the personal name <i>Mirhi</i> of unknown meaning. Bearers of this surname are both Muslims and Christians. Compare   Murray   5."]},{"name":"Murrey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"McMurray","meanings":["Irish (northern) and Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Muireadhaigh</b> or <b>Mac Muireadhaich</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Muireadhach</i> ‘seafarer’ (see   Murdoch  ). Compare   McCurry   1."]},{"name":"Murra","meanings":["Italian (Sicily): topographic name from Sicilian <i>murra</i> ‘large rock, mass of rocks’ or a habitational name from a place called with this word.","East Frisian: unexplained.","Albanian: nickname from <i>murrë</i> (definite form <i>murra</i>) ‘dark gray cow’."]},{"name":"Murrie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Murray  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Murray was born about 1158, in Haddingtonshire, Scotland. She had at least 1 son with Robert le Nae-peer."},"et":{"abt. 1158–":"umbes 1158–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1190–1300":"1190–1300","1158–Female":"1158–Surnud","1190":"1190","abt. 1158":"umbes 1158","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1158":"1158","1300":"1300","1180":"1180","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"abt. 1158–":"noin 1158–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1190–1300":"1190–1300","1158–Female":"1158–Kuollut","1190":"1190","abt. 1158":"noin 1158","about 1190":"noin 1190","1158":"1158","1300":"1300","1180":"1180","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"abt. 1158–":"environ 1158–Décédée","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1190–1300":"1190–1300","1158–Female":"1158–Décédée","1190":"1190","abt. 1158":"environ 1158","about 1190":"environ 1190","1158":"1158","1300":"1300","1180":"1180","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mary Murray est née environ 1158, à Haddingtonshire, Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert le Nae-peer."},"de":{"abt. 1158–":"um 1158–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","1190–1300":"1190–1300","1158–Female":"1158–Verstorben","1190":"1190","abt. 1158":"um 1158","about 1190":"um 1190","1158":"1158","1300":"1300","1180":"1180","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","lifeSummary":"Mary Murray wurde um 1158 in Haddin